                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.01/2216: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-16T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 16, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>859. From L’Heureux. AFHQ has instructed General MacFarlane to ask Badoglio for
                    an explanation of the reasons why without prior notification to the Allied
                    Control Commission the Italian Government took the initiative for exchanging
                    representatives with the Soviets. [L’Heureux.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
